@startuml
' @id(DOM-SYMBOL-SPAN)
' @desc(DOM-SYMBOL-SPAN, "A code symbol located by the syn engine: { path, symbol, line_start, line_end, kind }. symbol is a dotted path (e.g. MddViewer.apply_theme or Project.review_traceability) built from syn item names + impl self-type; kind is one of fn/struct/enum/impl/const/etc. Produced by CMP-TRACE-ENGINE from syn::parse_file + proc-macro2 span-locations; used to (a) resolve a source_link's symbol forward, and (b) find the enclosing symbol for a changed line range reverse.")
' @id(DOM-TRACE-REPORT)
' @desc(DOM-TRACE-REPORT, "Outcome of Project::review_traceability(): { forward_errors: [(model_id, path, symbol)], reverse_bucket_a: [(path, symbol_or_region, reason)], reverse_bucket_b: [(path, symbol)], matched: bool }. matched = forward_errors empty AND reverse_bucket_b empty (when traceability.parity_check = error). Folded into ReviewReport as the third pass; the combined ReviewReport.matched ANDs ID parity, security parity, and this.")
' @id(DOM-SOURCE-LINK)
' @desc(DOM-SOURCE-LINK, "The existing trace.yml record { model_id, path, symbol? } given a verified meaning by this cycle. model_id is a diagram @id; path a repo-relative source file; symbol an optional dotted symbol path resolvable by DOM-SYMBOL-SPAN. One @id may have many links; many @ids may share a (path, symbol). Forward parity verifies each resolves; reverse parity covers a changed symbol when some link's (path, symbol) matches it.")
' Objective-side domain for the traceability engine (cycle 0013):
' the symbol the syn index yields, the trace.yml record it verifies,
' and the report the gate produces.
title MDD traceability — domain (objective)

class SymbolSpan {
  + path : String
  + symbol : String
  + line_start : u32
  + line_end : u32
  + kind : SymbolKind
}

class SourceLink {
  + model_id : String
  + path : String
  + symbol : Option<String>
}

class TraceReport {
  + forward_errors : Vec<ForwardError>
  + reverse_bucket_a : Vec<ReverseWarn>
  + reverse_bucket_b : Vec<ReverseError>
  + matched : bool
}

SourceLink "1" ..> "0..1" SymbolSpan : resolves to >
TraceReport "1" o-- "*" SourceLink : verifies >

note bottom of SymbolSpan
  Built by syn::parse_file + proc-macro2
  span-locations. A changed line range maps to
  the SymbolSpan whose [line_start, line_end]
  contains it; lines outside any span are glue
  (escape hatch).
end note

note bottom of TraceReport
  matched = forward_errors.is_empty() AND
  reverse_bucket_b.is_empty() under
  traceability.parity_check = error; bucket A
  is informational (warn) either way.
end note
@enduml
